import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    box_data = data[data['location'].isin(['New York', 'Seattle'])]
    box_data = box_data[['location', 'precipitation']]
    
    ax = box_data.boxplot(by='location', column='precipitation')
    ax.set_title('')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of precipitation in New York and Seattle?')
    plt.suptitle('')
    plt.xlabel('Location')
    plt.ylabel('Precipitation')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    data_new_york = data[data['location'] == 'New York']
    data_seattle = data[data['location'] == 'Seattle']

    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.plot(data_new_york['date'], data_new_york['temp_max'], label='New York Temp Max', alpha=0.7)
    plt.plot(data_new_york['date'], data_new_york['temp_min'], label='New York Temp Min', alpha=0.7)
    plt.plot(data_seattle['date'], data_seattle['temp_max'], label='Seattle Temp Max', alpha=0.7)
    plt.plot(data_seattle['date'], data_seattle['temp_min'], label='Seattle Temp Min', alpha=0.7)

    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Temperature')
    plt.title('How does the temperature vary over time in New York and Seattle?')
    plt.legend()

    ax = plt.gca()
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)

    return plt

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    
    ny_data = data[data['location'] == 'New York']
    seattle_data = data[data['location'] == 'Seattle']
    
    plt.scatter(ny_data['wind'], ny_data['temp_max'], label='New York', alpha=0.5)
    plt.scatter(seattle_data['wind'], seattle_data['temp_max'], label='Seattle', alpha=0.5)
    
    plt.xlabel('Wind Speed')
    plt.ylabel('Max Temperature')
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the relationship between wind speed and temperature in New York and Seattle?', wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    weather_counts = data.groupby(['location', 'weather']).size().unstack()
    weather_counts.plot(kind='bar', rot=0)
    
    plt.title("What is the most common type of weather in New York and Seattle?")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```
